This paper deals with signal processing and wireless communications, which are typically associated with the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed algorithm also involves gradient descent and shrinkage steps, which are commonly used in Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper presents numerical results that involve solving optimization problems, which is a common theme in Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-category.
